gomodel:SYNGO_592  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: eIF-4E is involved in cap-dependent initation of translation (Fig. 1). Exaggerated expression of eIF-4E causes alterations in synaptic function, dendritic spine density and synaptic plasticity (Fig. 3).\n\n8/8/2017 Pim\n- eIF-4E KO shown to enhance translation and shown to have enhaced mPFC, striatal and hippocampal LTD. The LTD defects are rescued by application of a translation blocker (4EGI-1). These observations together fully support the selected term.. Experimental description: \"Generation of βT-Eif4e transgenic mice (eIF-4E transgenic mice) has been described previously ...\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9377-7414" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9880-1214" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0269-0311" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9681-3318" ;
        dc:date           "2017-08-09" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_592" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

